#1 Metastatic rectal carcinoma to nodes with FAP
PLAN
1.  I will see him again following his PET scan.
2.  I discussed treatment with chemotherapy with goals and side-effects.  I discussed the regimen of FOLFOX plus Avastin as first-line treatment.  He wants to get started on treatment and wishes it in 33919.  I called Dr. Terry Kernan to help set-up an appointment.  They will also set-up for a new baseline CT-scan to see response to treatment.  In addition, they will set him up for a Port-A-Cath.  I discussed the toxicities of FOLFOX plus Avastin.  I will see him again in two days following his PET scan.  We will not set-up a routine appointment for him but told him I would be happy to see him at any time, but he should be seen at some point when a decision would need to be made about possible change in treatment.
ADVANCE DIRECTIVES
Advance directive or living will: No, not interested in additional information.

